1. Sole Trader (self-employed) 
- Statutory requirements for establishment: A self-employed person is the simplest type of company, which does not need to be registered and only needs to run its own business activities. Self-employed people are required to comply with UK tax requirements, register as self-employed and pay personal income tax and national insurance.
2. Private Limited Company:
- Statutory conditions for incorporation: A private limited company needs to meet the following conditions:
- At least one shareholder and one director;
- Registered office address;
- Provide Articles of Association;
- The registered office must be a legal business address;
- Minimum registered capital of £1 and at least one share;
- Incorporated and registered through the Companies House.
3. Public Limited Company:
- Statutory establishment conditions: A public limited company needs to meet the following conditions:
- At least two shareholders and two directors;
- Articles of association;
- Registered office address;
- Minimum registered capital of £50,000, of which at least 25% of the shares must be subscribed;
- Incorporated and registered through a company registration authority.
